			<article>
				<h2>Video</h2>
				<p>With the exception of the Broken Ankles single Tollerated, there have been no official Girl Talk music videos made. This has prompted fans to make their own videos including a rotoscoped animation of a live show, mashup videos where videos of the sampled songs are spliced together in time with the music and a full album length music video dance movie.</p><br />
				<p>This rotoscoped concert video, biased on the track Bounce That from the album Night Ripper, was made by Professor Matthew Soar with help from his students at Concordia University as a contribution to the Open Source Cinema Project. It took three weeks of intensive work to produce and remains one of the most watched Girl Talk fan videos on YouTube.</p><br />
				<video width="640" height="360" controls="controls">
					<source src="../videos/bouncethat.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
